column5: Me and my boy and the father in law have done a few boat runs the last few weeks up on the Notty. Had lots of success and he’s continuing his trend of out fishing me  does it all by himself.  last time out lost a giant (I believe) went in under a bunch of sticks, was down there for a few minutes and ended up breaking me off. Good times
Nice pics, hopefully the young lad is hooked on this sport.
Oh ya, he is. Has no problem getting up and onto the river for 6ish lol.
It’s pretty crazy how low the water level is, I don’t remember it being this low. Hard to get over one of the dams with the boat.
LOW,,, aint the word. I can walk a 2 mile stretch with out bush wacking. Crazy low. Nice fishing there LF. Well done.
